<Author>claudinepersaud
<Content>camping Italia I stayed here with my son and partner for 5 nights. We rented a room for 3 which turned out to be a static caravan. The caravan was quite small but very clean and very well equipped and the attached outside kitchen was great and also well equipped  you get a decent sized fridge. The pool area was lovely and the restaurant good value.But I had two problems with this place1. There were signs everwhere saying dogs must be on leads which was well observed by everyone except for the campsites own 3 dogs which ran around unchecked in a pack attacking guests dogs, attacking each other and generally causing a nuisance. Staff didn't care one bit. 2. It was so hot and the caravan had no fan or aircond unit which made sleeping at night impossible and the mozzys were having a field day!despite all this i would recommend this place as good value as long as 1. your not afraid of dogs2. you don't go in the middle of the summer! 
